Among the items confiscated were two shotguns, a revolver and ammunition for an R5 rifle. JOHANNESBURG Eastern Cape police have taken two men into custody after confiscating an arms cache near the town of Mthatha.Police conducted a four-hour long operation in the village of Ngqeleni on Saturday, leading to the find.Among the items confiscated were two shotguns, a revolver and ammunition for an R5 rifle.A 50-year-old and 36-year-old were arrested during the operation.The police s Mzukisi Fatyela says, They were arrested during the early hours of yesterday. They are detained and will appear in court on Monday. 